HEADWORD: corybantic
<hw>cor`y*ban"tic</hw> <pr>(k?r`?-b?n"t?k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>Korybantiko`s</grk>, fr. <grk>Kory`bas</grk> a Corybant.]</ety>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or resembling, the Corybantes or their rites;
frantic; frenzied; <as>as, a <ex>corybantic</ex> dance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

